What we could pay for over the next year if we cut the military budget by 10%: 
✅ 684,855,233 COVID Tests &amp; 
✅ 820,000 Hospital Stays for COVID-19 &amp; 
✅ 788,461 People receiving $600 weekly unemployment payments

It’s past time we end wasteful spending &amp; invest in the people.

Black women must be protected &amp; respected. This isn’t a controversial statement, it’s a fact. 

@theestallion speaking truth to power. 

 https://t.co/jIdJt6YX4n

Trump has made clear that he will pick a nominee who is committed to overturning Roe v. Wade &amp; taking away reproductive rights.

As Co-Chairs of the Pro-Choice Caucus
@RepDianaDeGette &amp; I are calling on the Senate to wait to consider any nominee until a new president is installed https://t.co/ukh8Pjdlgb

The Pentagon used $1 billion in Cares Act funds to pay defense contractors instead of keeping troops and the general public safe. This is unconscionable. 

@RepMarkPocan and I are calling for this to be investigated immediately. 

https://t.co/7PxMXKxL4D

It’s past time that this legislative body understand that women of color are here to stay. 

@RepAOC is here to stay.

And we're getting things done. https://t.co/ESU16yvcJ6

Almost 50 million people have filed for unemployment in the past six months. Many face the threat of eviction. 

This is a national crisis. 

@senatemajldr must pass the HEROES Act NOW.

We are in the middle of a pandemic. Millions across the country are facing unemployment and cannot afford rent. 

That’s why I’m working to extend the moratorium on evictions set to expire this month. 

@senatemajldr must step up and finally act on our bills to provide relief.
